</div>


<div class="post" id="piece_three">
	<h1 onclick='show_default("piece_three")' class="go_back_btn">
		<i class="fas fa-arrow-left" style="margin-right: 3px;"></i> Go Back 
	</h1>
	<h3 class="piece_header"> <%= @title4 %> </h3>
	<p>
The sky, a turquoise blue <br>
Singes the eye. <br>
The suburbs, across the harbour <br>
are clear of smog today. <br>
The grey buildings retreat <br>
under the onslaught of <br>
the magenta and yellow <br>
bougainvillea and the dusty <br>
road dividers surrender to <br>
bright blades of feisty grass. <br>
The pastel pink baby leaves play <br>
with the cheerful skipping wind, <br>
giddy children run and sing <br>
and the ragged, jagged city of Mumbai <br>
Enjoys its brief tryst with Spring. <br>
	</p>
	<div class="powered_by"> Powered by WordGates | The Home of Writers. </div>
</div>


<div class="post" id="piece_four">
	<h1 onclick='show_default("piece_four")' class="go_back_btn">
		<i class="fas fa-arrow-left" style="margin-right: 3px;"></i> Go Back 
	</h1>
	<h3 class="piece_header"> <%= @title5 %></h3>
	<p>
I am transparent like water. <br>
You do not see me. <br>
Do not see the light refracted through me <br>
as you sit there and eat your omelette <br>
with the absorption of an infant with it’s toes. <br>
 <br>
I am fluid like water. <br>
I flow through the house <br>
silently. You do not hear me. <br>
I am not a bubbly spring or a crashing wave. <br>
I am maybe rain falling on a lawn. <br>
 <br>
I am still like water  <br>
frozen on a pond. <br>
You don’t realize my presence. <br>
You notice me only when your laundry is late <br>
or the ‘koftas’ are not as soft as your mother’s. <br>
 <br>
I am flavourless like water. <br>
I leave no bitter aftertaste,  <br>
just a lime deposit in the kettle. <br>
But that won’t make a difference to you <br>
rushing to the loo with your teacup. <br>
 <br>
I am water. Be careful. <br>
I will be the tsunami you won’t see <br>
Till it’s upon you, <br>
absorbed as you are in your phone. <br>
And then it will be too late. <br>
	</p>
